d just wrap his apron up, chuck it under the - put his clothes on and he was a wonderful walker me father you know, you might have heard Tommy Blackwater used to be - always used to say to me, you're more like your father every day, you know. He was a won
d
erful walker and he'd walk from here to the Royal to see this young little lad and back again, right up to the - well I can remember the day he came home and said he was dead, you know. But - I - I've only got a very vague memory of - of the funeral like,
 happen it was just one coach you know which carried the little coffin in -
