t you know, and they had more - much more than I had. And - it was - it you know, it took a lot of - a lot of time to - well like there's one chap now, he's in the pensions with me now, he's a fortnight younger than me. He's on the eighteenth of October a
s I'm on the third and I suppose like you know, he's got more pounds now than I've got buttons. But his - his people like were great {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}
 - dairy people - they've always had money you see, and he's used to money. Oh me father liked his pint but I never saw him drunk.
