Yes, at the Boys Brigade lads - after - up 'til ten - no, I lied - until I was about ten I'd say I'd be just ran a bit ragged with the - school pals. And then
 after I joined the choir and joined the Boys Brigade us - Wavertree then was like my home instead of Old Swan like, see we first lived in Old Swan. The shop was just four blocks - four houses in Old Swan, well Binns Road separated Wavertree and then I sp
e
nt my time in Wavertree the same as these pals you see and 'cos after I was twelve football would at the Boys Brigade and following them around and - doing all lots of other things. And - well Friday night - Friday night would be choir practice night you 
