Yes. I only once had like any personal contact with anything like that - it was - ay - a relation of the wife's - the parents died and the lads were in the orphanage you know at Thingwall. O
ne - one lad I was bringing him out to - to a job - he'd got a job here at Crawfords and - he was in the printers and - I saw the way that home turned him out like, when - when they were sending him out from the home and they gave him a suitcase with - he
 
had a suit that he was wearing and a suit to change and everything - in - shirts and no matter. It was a wonderful turn out you know from the home, yes, to - to give the lad a start you know. Well it was really good that. That - that's my only personal co
ntact with any of those sort of things.
