The when my - oh I don't know, it'd be - you know, perhaps a shilling or some - one and threepence, something like that. Then when my elder brother started working he went into a shop in Prescott Road and I used to sometimes run down to the shop stand at
 the doorway when he went on an errand I went with him until - I was - I don't know how old I would be but not more than ten the - boss of this - shop - a man named Dobson called me in one day and said, here you can go on this message. And from that I got
 - a night job after school - that were only about - something like half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did you like that job?
