Well when I - like first left school I went to - to a bakery at that corner of Binns Road which was owned by a man named Oldham. I was - a shop lad you know a
nd - of course in them days the hours were very long - they were from about eight o'clock in the morning 'til - oh, eight or nine at night and Saturday I could get well on 'til midnight. And I - I was there until - I wouldn't actually know how long but I 
was there until I had a - a severe dose of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4087616\charrsid3029110 diphtheria}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 What did you have to do in the job?
