\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh - escapes me memory now. Until I was sixteen. And then very fairly like she said to me, well now - there doesn't seem to be much hope here for you getting on 
at sixteen and she said, I - I think it's time you - you were like - looked for a little something better. And I was at time watching the paper and I - I had in mind - I'd read - Morrison Jones in town were advertising like for young people to sort of lea
rn the - but at that time I was serving Mrs McCulloch in Logan Road and -
