16, it snowed, it hailed, it bloody did everything. And we had a terrible mess up like, one fellow grew and boredom - what was that then - now - the following - we went back up the line to - went down to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11798229\charrsid3029110 Honare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110  because the horses were in a bit of bad co
ndition we went down there and we were down there about three months and we went back up the line to where - to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11798229\charrsid3029110 Apres}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110  - to - and - I can't remember now where we were in wagon lines. I was in the ammunition column you see by then. 'Course see we didn't take }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
