No. From there I - I came - my doctor - I spent Christmas there - had a very nice time there, Christmas, and you all, you know, those that were able sang a song and I was the opthalmical 
ward see 'cos my - one eye was out and - there was chaps there who'd - got all sorts of medals - V.Cis and medals and all that and they used to pray me not to have their eyes put in you know. But everybody you see was able to walk about and we all did a j
ob in the - in the hospital. From there like I came home like had leave and I went back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Winchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And I reported there to a battery and - make yourself comfortable he said to parade in the morning. Well the next morning I was on parade and the first th
ing they did was to send me in the riding school see. The - the riding master here was - a Major - he only had one eye and he'd got a very bad name - they said, ooh, what you going - and we were in the school and he - he came to me and he asked me what - 
m
ob I was in and - all right, we went on. Well when I got back to the - camp from the ride we dismounted, after dinner we came through and he said, you've no rights to be here. I said, well - this is where I was sent on my papers and I reported in yesterda
y
 to you. He said, yes, but they made a mistake, you shouldn't be here, you should be down the road at Wylines. And evidently there was a distinction between regular people and these people who'd been in Territorials you see. So back I went to Wylimes. Pac
k
ed up again you know, went down and the next morning they said, well you're on the - on the ride. I said, I - I went through the ride yesterday - the at the others - other - camp. He said, all right, well you're on the drive. See that - you had to pass yo
u
r driving licence then. So I went up to this gun team and this Major - he detailed out - you're ammunition carrying this morning see. So you signalled to the six - six teams you see are lined up and you - he gives you the signal for you've got to - the id
