\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did you have any special friends at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Yes, boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Where would you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh well, up the - until I joined the Army of course like as I say it was the football and the cricket and the Boys Brigade and that that filled our time. It was after that we - fell into more specialised things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did you have to be home at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Yes, that's what I was just saying - half past nine you see. Unless I asked permissi
on you see, if we were going out on a Saturday evening say with the boys - six or seven of us going out - you see I would tell me father where we were going - it would probably be the last house of the Pavilion, see, and that was all right. He knew where 
we were he knew that who we were with
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
and she did something wrong you know and - and I forget - he - he made some - explanation you know, it so upset her that she - that she - she started crying. Of course father was a bit sorry then because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 But he didn't take any interest in gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 You did tell me about playing draughts, snakes and ladders and ludo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Ah yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did you play games outside and if so did your parents ever play with you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 No, not - n
ot at that time, you see, my father knew - me father was very interested bear in mind in what we did - particularly like so that one of me young brothers he wanted him to become a runner, he said he had the - all the makers of a runner you know, but he - 
h
e - he wasn't as interested as me father was in it. But - oh me father was very interested. Oh I know he used to take photographs of me and me Boys Brigade and that to the pub to show his mates in the pub. Because he always went for a drink every night yo
u know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 You never drank did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Not - not to say drink. I don't mind if I go out and anybody then invites you to have a drink, just for the sake of hospitality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 I've never seen you drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh yes, I - I - I don't mind -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 I don't dr
ink myself - I drink very little myself but I thought you drank even less than I do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
No, perhaps more than you do and you see we go away Christmas time you see and we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 What class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh working class wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 You would say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh aye. Ne - never above. I suppose me father having been - a shopkeeper - it was - you know - we ought to have been but - I - I was speaking to a chap in the boot repairing business today and you know in them days it was v
ery hard going wasn't it. You see, this sort of weather, they abhorred it - it was no good to them because me father said in those days the people particularly around here, the kids would run around in their bare feet and it didn't wear shoes out you see.
 
So as soon as the - the bad weather came, the snow, me father loved the snow because of course as he said, the snow found all the crinnies and crannies and cracks in their shoes and they had to have them repaired and that was the only time he made money a
nd then the majority of times they - they'd forget to come and take them in or pay for them. I often think that if everybody had paid up to my father we shouldn't have been badly off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 There was an awful lot of tick in those days wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 People in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} won't know what tick is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
What does it mean - give the wire? Tick is credit. Did I ask you did you come into contact with any employers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh - yes, like my - the job before I went to Crawfords, you see, 
when I was about fourteen I had a very bad dose - of - diphtheria and it was all in me throat you know and - I was in Mill Lane Hospital here you know for some months with it and I always blamed that - you see, I think I might have made something as a sin
g
er if I hadn't had that - I - I think that was because we were doing very well with the - you see, the top four boys, we used to go to this Mr Kinsey's house every Saturday morning for a couple of hours lessons you see and voice production and things and 
-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 How many boys in the choir altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh we used to have eight on each side - sixteen boys - that's right - that's right, yes. Yes, we used to have about four men each side and there ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 I joined my choir just when the war started you
 see and the men had been called up. I finished up the second from top on the decanal side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh I now - of course I led out front for many years. Of course I - I joined the choir when I was ten you see and - and I went until I was - nineteen I think. 
And when I - just beginning to - to go into the choir to learn to be a tenor when, of course the war broke and we went off you see. When I came back, the man who was there then - of course the - the - Mr Kinsey had been interred you see, being a German, a
nd never heard any more of him, I don't know what became of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 The war was a terrible thing wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Did you meet any of the employers at Crawfords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Well first you see I went to a Miss Smith in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Edge Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Originally like her f
ather it was her father's business or his - they were grocers and bakers and - it was very nice job and they were very nice people and - I - I was very - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1051982\charrsid3029110 save}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110  it, I was very well liked by these Smiths and it was only when I was sixteen you see as Miss Sm
ith said to me, well look, I think you're getting a bit old for the shop now and I can't offer you anything better. Don't you think you'd better look for something different you see. And at that time we were serving Mr McCulloch's wice, see, and Mrs McCul
l
och said to me, would you like to go to Crawfords? And I said, ooh, very much. I've tried to get in there before, see, and if you remember Mr Owens at that time, see, I went to see him this morning - on this Monday morning and there were - they - oh I sho
u
ld think at least a dozen there after a job you know. And, he said no more, nobody this morning, you know. I said, I'm the boy Mr McCulloch sent. Oh he said, well, all I can offer you he said, you'll have to start in Mr McCulloch's department. I said, wel
l that's what I want. And that was how I started at Crawfords. So these - these Smithes - there was Miss Janet Smith, Miss Agenes Smith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Who did they mix up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
They were great church people, you see, they were Scotch and they were great church people but Mr Coxall who }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1444940 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
 Miss Agnes - they had one son - he was what they called in them days a first class clerk in the Mersey Docks and Harbour Board which was in them days a very good position. I used to meet them an awful lot after I left them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Who do you think they mixed up with though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Well they had their own set of friends you know - the - they were mostly business people that they - palled in with. Because they - they had - I should say like what was in them days of - a fair amount of money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
I'd like to know what you thought about the middle class people and what jobs the middle class people had in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Well you see I should say - I should have thought that these people were middle class people. They - they were 
not - you know - into the awfully well off people who could afford to live without doing anything. They had to do something you see so I should have thought - I should have thought that they were the middle class.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 The chap who was in the office job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 That was your impression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Yes. But - you see, on the other hand - she had a brother who lived in Waterloo who - how he got his money I don't know but in some sort of business but I should have said he was practically a step above
 them because he could afford so much more than they could and - in fact I think in them days he had a car, which was a great thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 You said a Miss Home found sewing for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Miss - that was Miss Helm. She was the lady reader in th
e church you know. She was a great old dame. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 How much sewing did your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh an awful lot. Oh an awful lot. And when - when the first war broke out and - if you remember they used to have sewing classes didn't she and I think she tau
ght St Mary's - womens - what did they call it - the mothers meeting - taught all the women there how to cut out and make shirts. And of course when Crawfords started supplying the girls with overalls she made the first overalls at Crawfords. Used to sew 
flour bags - they used to send. I sued to take a dozen home like, even after the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 And she would be paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 That was Mrs - Mrs Jackson, yes. Oh yes, they paid her for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Would you tell me about your father's great mistake - don't 
tell me if you don't want to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Well there - there's no shame in it like so far as I'm concerned. It - it - it was this that - you see, my father belonged to this club in - in St Oswell Street, in - it wasn't St Os - off - I forget -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Derby Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
No. Opposite the omnibus - the omnibus used to be on the corner of - what street was it called - oh - anyway, he belonged to this club, Victoria Club you see and it had been raided several times but you see it was always in the daytime when me father 
would be working. But they knew because - and - and I would repeat this in any court in - in - in England - they knew that my father was a member there because he used to go to Derby Lane to collect the police boots to repair them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Derby Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was the police station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
That's right. And of course you know the - the firemen lived above in them days and that didn't they. And several policeman used to come - visit our house on the Sunday evening. And - my father used to play, of course in them days, a 
lot of billiards and it came about that one time he was in the semi-final of the Liverpool championship here, played - on that club, if you'll remember was - was a big house in Kensington just before you got to Mill Hill. A big house there. It was a Conse
r
vative club. Now he was playing there this night and he was playing a policeman. And on all known form as I understand it like only being a lad at that time - on all known form as far as I understand it my father should have won easy - odds on like you se
e
. And they - tempted him to delay his game and to play below to give the man a lead whilst they got - bets on I presume you see and - it come unstuck - for me father couldn't get going when he-ought to have got going and he got beaten. Now the - the upsho
t
 of that was that I - like this - this is what I think like was the sequence up to it was that - round November - it would be November because I'm sure I'd turned fourteen - I was at home, you see, I wasn't at school, I was at home. That's what makes me t
hink I was about fourteen. But I can't tell you the year now. Because all these things, at that time it was the Liverpool Post, you remember, the Mercury and Post in them days wasn't there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Liverpool Weekly Post?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 That's right. Well we had - well
 - well Mercury was one. Well we had all the cuttings you see of this but I - but they - they somehow became lost. I don't know what became of them. I would like to have them. But the outcome of it was - yes well the outcome of it was this. That this day 
there was I was in the kitchen. My mother was over the road in a friend of ours - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Andersons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in - that's in the stores up her now like - provision shop. And there was this scuffle in the lobby of the shop you see and I run - like to see what was up and what 
I could see was about four men had grabbed another man in - in the lobby, you see, my father was sitting at his finishing bench on the other side. And all I heard them say was - my father said, well it looks like a ball that the kids have made - playing w
i
th you see. They'd fished out this bundle of papers tied with string - the police. And - then this man said to my father, well I'm afraid I'll have to ask you to come to the station. See. So me father said, well you'll have to wait until I wash and shave 
myself. Was - all right. So they took him off. And the next day he was - tried with - for running a - bet -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 -Giving bets - taking bets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Yes, yes, making illegal use you see. So - a man named Mr Howard, the coal merchant up - here and a man named 
Mr Corner who ran the - his wife had this shop few doors away from us, they want bail for him. He was on a week's bail you see. And - each time he was brought up the police said they were not prepared to go on with the case. And this went on for about - f
o
ur or five weeks 'til in the end the day before he should go again the next time you see my father said to these men - I - I remember like this you see my mother told me afterwards - he said to them, now I want no bail tomorrow. If they remand me again I'
l
l do - I'll go to goal. So this was what happened - see. And of course I always remember him saying every morning that they came they had to give him what he wanted for breakfast and that and the papers and that, and then he - when he finally came up the 
f
ollowing time, the police like gave all their evidence, I don't know what it was and - then I believe Stewart Deacon said to my father - haven't you got anything to say? See. And he said, all I want - he said, is for the police to produce the man that the
y arrested in the shop. Of course he said to the policeman like who - the - I suppose he'd be an inspector - well, can you produce the man? And he said, I'm sorry to say we can't. He was employed by the police. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 The police said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Yes. See
 what they'd done - they'd got a man - yes, what they'd done, they'd got this man - a policeman - to dress in railway clothes and come into the shop to make the bets. I always remember the paper, across the top it had big snub for the Liverpool police.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 And your dad was found ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 Oh, he was discharged. You see, yes. And he let it go you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 He let it go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Oh that's what I said there was 1- I should think at least twenty people must have written from all over England - to take the case. And he wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7157778 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 That's where you think he made the mistake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8401235 TC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4223140\charrsid3029110 
Just out - oh yes, just out of loyalty to the - to the fellows that he played billiards and that with and perhaps drunk with. He could have - they said like he had a fine chance of making money on it. Yes.
